  "description": "The reactor-side plumbing that makes decentralized channels possible: operation log, IChannel mailboxes, sync tables, and multi-remote support.",
  "orientation": "This MOC captures the reactor sync primitives that every transport \u2014 GraphQL or Swarm \u2014 composes with. Operations-as-append-only-log is the substrate; IChannel mailboxes (inbox/outbox/deadLetter) are the per-remote seam; SyncManager persists state in PGlite tables (remotes, cursors, dead letters, and the mailbox buffer); and multi-remote-per-collection is the switch that enables the dual-sync strategy. These notes form the backbone needed to reason about the SwarmChannel, debouncing, and recovery.",
